# ðŸ§¬ Multi-Omics Data Preprocessing in R

This repository contains R scripts to preprocess **methylation**, **transcriptomics**, and **miRNA** datasets for multi-omics analysis. Each dataset is log-transformed, imputed (if needed), scaled, and exported for downstream tasks like MOFA or clustering.

## ðŸ“¦ Required R Libraries

```r
library(readxl)
library(minfi)
library(IlluminaHumanMethylationEPICanno.ilm10b4.hg19)
library(IlluminaHumanMethylationEPICmanifest)
library(FlowSorted.Blood.EPIC)
library(GeneNet)
library(limma)
library(GenomicRanges)
library(data.table)
library(tidyverse)
library(zoo)
library(lattice)
library(ggplot2)
library(reshape)
library(stringr)
library(RColorBrewer)
library(mixOmics)
library(pROC)
library(biomaRt)
library(org.Hs.eg.db)
library(entropy)
library(impute)
library(MOFA2)
```

